This article is a message from the President of the United States, Barack Obama, to Congress regarding a proposed Agreement for Cooperation between the United States and China concerning peaceful uses of nuclear energy. The agreement aims to facilitate the transfer of material, equipment, information, and technology for nuclear research and power production between the two countries while ensuring nonproliferation measures are met. The proposed agreement has been negotiated in accordance with applicable laws and is believed to advance the nonproliferation and foreign policy interests of the United States. China has demonstrated its commitment to nonproliferation through its participation in various treaties and conventions. The President has reviewed the agreement and determined that its performance will promote the common defense and security without posing an unreasonable risk. The President urges Congress to give the agreement favorable consideration. The agreement will undergo a review process by the Senate Foreign Relations Committee and the House Foreign Affairs Committee.